  "prompt": "How much refund will I get on my PRS counter ticket if my seat is waitlisted even after the departure of the train? Can I board the train using it",
  "response": "If your PRS (Passenger Reservation System) counter ticket is waitlisted and has not been confirmed or upgraded to RAC (Reservation Against Cancellation) by the time of the train's departure, you are not allowed to board the train with that ticket. In such cases, you are eligible for a refund.\n\nAccording to Indian Railways rules, if a waitlisted ticket is not confirmed, the passenger is entitled to a full refund. To claim this refund, you need to surrender the ticket at the booking counter or file a Ticket Deposit Receipt (TDR) online, depending on how the ticket was booked, within the stipulated time frames set by Indian Railways.\n\nRemember, it's important to check the latest guidelines from Indian Railways or consult with the railway station for the most accurate and current information, as rules and policies can change.",
